<p>I have to write a function that will read an array of structures of type <code>Product</code> with data from a binary file.This file contains the number of products - <code>nr</code> and a number of articles of type <code>Product</code>. What's wrong? Thank you in advance!</p>  <pre><code>#define SIZE 30  typedef struc{     int id;     char[SIZE] name;     float price; }Product;  void create(Product *p, FILE *fptr) {     p = malloc(sizeof(Product));     fread(p, 1, sizeof(Product), fptr); }  int main(int argc, char* argv[]) {     FILE *fptr = fopen(argv[1],"rb");     Product *p;     create(p, fptr);      return 0; } </code></pre>  <hr>